-- BP Pledges Its Shares in Russia's Rosneft for $2 Billion Loan, WSJ Reports
-- Ilya Khrennikov
-- 2010-06-28T03:59:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/bp-pledges-its-shares-in-russia-s-rosneft-for-2-billion-loan-wsj-reports.html

          
          
             BP Plc pledged its shares in OAO
Rosneft, Russia’s biggest oil producer, to secure a $2 billion
loan to help fix the oil spill in the Gulf of Mexico, the Wall
Street Journal reported.  
 The U.K.-based company owns 1.25 percent of Rosneft shares,
worth about $840 million, according to Russia’s Vedomosti daily.  
